# Sourced by the X session before the WM starts; everything in the
# session inherits these.

# Qt apps outside KDE (quickshell's tray menus, pavucontrol-qt, ...) have
# no platform theme under awesome and default to light Fusion.
#
# qt6ct rather than xdgdesktopportal: the portal theme supplies a color
# scheme but never an icon theme, so Qt's icon lookup finds nothing and
# Quickshell.iconPath() returns image://icon URLs that fail to load.
# qt6ct feeds Qt both. The trade-off is that it reads a static config
# instead of following the portal live, so system-theme-apply rewrites
# that file's color scheme on every dark/light toggle (it also creates
# the file, so this needs no tracked copy).
export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct
